"script": "A submarine weighs thousands of tons, yet it can dive deep and float back up whenever it wants. So how does a steel giant choose whether to sink? The secret is hollow tanks built into its hull. To dive, the crew opens valves and lets seawater flood those tanks, making the sub heavier than the water around it. Then it slips beneath the surface. To rise, they blast compressed air in, shoving all that water back out. And this simple swap between water and air is the only thing keeping the crew off the crushing seafloor.",
